article.headline: Bradley 68, Evansville 60
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. (AP) -- Marcellus Sommerville scored 22 points as Bradley beat Evansville 68-60 Wednesday night at Carver Arena. Bradley (10-12, 3-8 Missouri Valley) took a 28-22 lead at the half and hung on in the second half. The Braves got help from James Gillingham with 21 points and Mike Suggs with 10. The difference for Bradley was at the foul line where they converted 26-of-41 while Evansville was 7-of-19. The Braves countered a cold shooting night by turning 15 offensive rebounds into 20 points. Bradley went on a 17-5 run and took a 59-49 lead with 4:49 left after back-to-back 3-pointers by Joey Paul. Evansville couldn't get closer than seven points the rest of the way. Evansville (3-16, 2-9) was led by Clint Cuffle with 16 points. Justin Petty and Kyle Anslinger each scored 11. Sommerville led the Braves with nine rebounds and Suggs grabbed seven.
